1433 void FtpClientWorker::Release (int result, const char* const msg [], const char* api, int errnum)
1434 {
1435  char buffer [2048];
1436  if (m_released)
1437  return;
1438  m_released = true;

1440  Send (m_ctrlTask, new SftpClientStop ());
1441  m_ctrlTask = 0;
1442 
1443  buffer [0] = 0;
1444  bool sepind = false;
1445  sprintf (buffer, "S%06ld: --- released (code = %d, ", m_sessionId % (1000 * 1000), result);
1446  if (msg != 0)
1447  while (*msg != 0)
1448  {
1449  sprintf (buffer, "%s%s", buffer, *msg++);
1450  sepind = true;
1451  }
1452  if (api != 0)
1453  {
1454  if (sepind)
1455  strcat (buffer, ", ");
1456  sprintf (buffer, "%s'%s' failed", buffer, api);
1457  sepind = true;
1458  }
1459  if (errnum != 0)
1460  {
1461  if (sepind)
1462  strcat (buffer, ", ");
1463  sprintf (buffer, "%serrno = %d", buffer, errnum);
1464  }
1465  strcat (buffer, ")");
1466  cf_sc_printf (SC_SFTP, (result != 0) ? SC_ERR : SC_APL, "%s", buffer);
1467 }

1483 void FtpClientWorker::Execute (FtpRequest* req, void* addInfo)
1484 {
1485  char* reqtxt = FtpRequestInterface::GetFtpRequestText (req, '\t', '\n');
1486  FtpCallback* scenario;
1487 
1488  ++m_jobCount;
1489  m_sessionId = ++g_sessionId;
1490  m_ftpRequest = req;
1491  m_ftpConnectionInfo = &req->connection;
1492  switch (m_requestCode = req->request.requestCode)
1493  {
1494  case CheckConnectivity:
1495  m_checkConnectivity = &req->request.FtpRequestUnion_u.checkConnectivity;
1496  scenario = g_checkConnectivityScenario;
1497  break;
1498  case MakeDir:
1499  m_makeDir = &req->request.FtpRequestUnion_u.makeDir;
1500  scenario = g_mkdirScenario;
1501  break;
1502  case GetDir:
1503  m_getDir = &req->request.FtpRequestUnion_u.getDir;
1504  scenario = g_getdirScenario;
1505  break;
1506  case StoreFile:
1507  m_storeFile = &req->request.FtpRequestUnion_u.storeFile;
1508  scenario = g_storeScenario;
1509  break;
1510  case RetrieveFile:
1511  m_retrieveFile = &req->request.FtpRequestUnion_u.retrieveFile;
1512  scenario = g_retrieveScenario;
1513  break;
1514  case StoreAllFiles:
1515  m_storeAllFiles = &req->request.FtpRequestUnion_u.storeAllFiles;
1516  scenario = g_storeAllScenario;
1517  break;
1518  case RetrieveAllFiles:
1519  m_retrieveAllFiles = &req->request.FtpRequestUnion_u.retrieveAllFiles;
1520  scenario = g_retrieveAllScenario;
1521  break;
1522  case DeleteFile:
1523  m_deleteFile = &req->request.FtpRequestUnion_u.deleteFile;
1524  scenario = g_deleteScenario;
1525  break;
1526  case DeleteAllFiles:
1527  m_deleteAllFiles = &req->request.FtpRequestUnion_u.deleteAllFiles;
1528  scenario = g_deleteAllScenario;
1529  break;
1530  case MakeWorkingEnv:
1531  m_makeWorkingEnv = &req->request.FtpRequestUnion_u.makeWorkingEnv;
1532  scenario = g_makeWorkingEnvScenario;
1533  break;
1534  case CleanDir:
1535  m_cleanDir = &req->request.FtpRequestUnion_u.cleanDir;
1536  scenario = g_cleanDirScenario;
1537  break;
1538  default:
1539  scenario = 0;
1540  m_emptyRequest = &req->request.FtpRequestUnion_u.empty;
1541  break;
1542  }
1543  if (reqtxt != 0)
1544  {
1545  Send (m_ctrlTask, new SftpJobInfo (clientId (), m_jobCount, m_sessionId, reqtxt));
1546  free (reqtxt);
1547  }
1548  else
1549  Send (m_ctrlTask,
1550  new SftpJobInfo (clientId (), m_jobCount, m_sessionId, (char*) "CANNOT GENERATE FTP REQUEST DESCRIPTION"));
1551 
1552  Continue (scenario);
1553 }

1555 void FtpClientWorker::Continue (FtpCallback* scenario)
1556 {
1557  if (scenario == 0)
1558  {
1559  Stop ();
1560 // Release (0, 0, 0, 0);
1561  return;
1562  }
1563 
1564  m_released = false;
1565  if (IsAlive () && (strcmp (m_ftpConnectionInfo->hostname, (char*) m_name.c_str ()) == 0))
1566  {
1567  RegisterFtpScenario (scenario, this);
1568  ++m_connContinued;
1569  m_cwdContext = CWD_HOME_DIR;
1570  ChangeWorkingDirectory (m_homeDir.c_str ());
1571  }
1572  else
1573  {
1574  Stop ();
1575 // Release (0, 0, 0, 0);
1576  RegisterFtpScenario (scenario, this);
1577  m_name = m_ftpConnectionInfo->hostname;
1578  Start ();
1579  }
1580 }

1663 void FtpClientWorker::Common_StartupEventHandler (FtpClient *ftp, FtpContext context, FtpStatus status, FtpState state,
1664  void* args [])
1665 {
1666  in_addr_t hostAddr;
1667  sockaddr_in* sockaddr4 = 0;
1668  sockaddr_in6* sockaddr6 = 0;
1669 
1670  for (addrinfo* results = m_addrinfo; results != 0; results = results->ai_next)
1671  {
1672  if (results->ai_socktype != SOCK_DGRAM)
1673  continue;
1674  switch (results->ai_family)
1675  {
1676  case AF_INET:
1677  sockaddr4 = (sockaddr_in*) results->ai_addr;
1678  break;
1679  case AF_INET6:
1680  sockaddr6 = (sockaddr_in6*) results->ai_addr;
1681  break;
1682  }
1683  }
1684 
1685  char buff [64];
1686 
1687  if (sockaddr4 != 0)
1688  {
1689  ++m_connInited;
1690  cf_sc_printf (SC_SFTP, SC_APL, "--- starting A: (%s)", inet_ntop (AF_INET, &sockaddr4->sin_addr, buff, 64));
1691 
1692  sockaddr_in addr;
1693  memset (&addr, 0, sizeof(struct sockaddr_in));
1694  addr.sin_family = AF_INET;
1695  addr.sin_port = htons (IPPORT_FTP);
1696  addr.sin_addr = sockaddr4->sin_addr;
1697  ftp->Connect (m_ftpConnectionInfo->hostname, (sockaddr*) &addr, sizeof(sockaddr_in));
1698  }
1699  else if (sockaddr6 != 0)
1700  {
1701  ++m_connInited;
1702  cf_sc_printf (SC_SFTP, SC_APL, "--- starting AAAA: (%s)",
1703  inet_ntop (AF_INET6, &sockaddr6->sin6_addr, buff, 64));
1704 
1705  sockaddr_in6 addr;
1706  memset (&addr, 0, sizeof(struct sockaddr_in6));
1707  addr.sin6_family = AF_INET;
1708  addr.sin6_port = htons (IPPORT_FTP);
1709  addr.sin6_addr = sockaddr6->sin6_addr;
1710  ftp->Connect (m_ftpConnectionInfo->hostname, (sockaddr*) &addr, sizeof(sockaddr_in6));
1711  }
1712  else if ((hostAddr = inet_addr (m_ftpConnectionInfo->hostname)) != (in_addr_t) -1)
1713  {
1714  ++m_connInited;
1715  cf_sc_printf (SC_SFTP, SC_APL, "--- starting AA: (%s)", m_ftpConnectionInfo->hostname);
1716 
1717  sockaddr_in addr;
1718  memset (&addr, 0, sizeof(struct sockaddr_in));
1719  addr.sin_family = AF_INET;
1720  addr.sin_port = htons (IPPORT_FTP);
1721  addr.sin_addr.s_addr = hostAddr;
1722  ftp->Connect (m_ftpConnectionInfo->hostname, (sockaddr*) &addr, sizeof(sockaddr_in));
1723  }
1724  else
1725  {
1726  ++m_connUnresolved;
1727  const char* const args [] =
1728  { "unresolved hostname: ", m_ftpConnectionInfo->hostname, 0 };
1729  Release (FtpUnresolvedHostname, args, 0, 0);
1730  }
1731 // else ftp->Connect(m_ftpConnectionInfo->hostname);
1732 }
1733 
1734 void FtpClientWorker::Common_ConnectedEventHandler (FtpClient *ftp, FtpContext context, FtpStatus status,
1735  FtpState state, void* args [])
1736 {
1737  size_t pos;
1738 
1739  ++m_connEstablished;
1740  cf_sc_printf (SC_SFTP, SC_APL, "--- connected: %s", m_ftpConnectionInfo->hostname);
1741  string authentication = m_ftpConnectionInfo->authentication;
1742  if ((pos = authentication.find ("ssl-version=", 0)) == string::npos)
1743  ftp->Login (m_ftpConnectionInfo->user, m_ftpConnectionInfo->password);
1744  else
1745  {
1746  size_t spos = authentication.find (';', pos);
1747  if (spos == string::npos)
1748  ftp->Login (m_ftpConnectionInfo->user, m_ftpConnectionInfo->password);
1749  else
1750  {
1751  string sslVersion = authentication.substr (pos + 12, spos);
1752  if (sslVersion == "none")
1753  ftp->Login (m_ftpConnectionInfo->user, m_ftpConnectionInfo->password);
1754  else
1755  {

1767  else

1769  }

1773  }

1927 void FtpClientWorker::Mkdir_CwdFinishedEventHandler (FtpClient *ftp, FtpContext context, FtpStatus status,
1928  FtpState state, void* args [])
1929 {
1930  switch (m_cwdContext)
1931  {
1932  case CWD_HOME_DIR:
1933  m_cwdContext = CWD_REMOTE_DIR;
1934  ftp->ChangeWorkingDirectory (m_makeDir->remoteDirName);
1935  break;
1936  case CWD_REMOTE_DIR:
1937  m_mkdEnd = m_mkdPtr = m_makeDir->remoteDirName;
1938  while (*m_mkdEnd == '/')
1939  *m_mkdEnd++ = 0;
1940  if (m_mkdEnd != m_mkdPtr)
1941  {
1942  m_cwdContext = CWD_ROOT;
1943  ftp->ChangeWorkingDirectory ("/");
1944  }
1945  else
1946  {
1947  while ((*m_mkdEnd != 0) && (*m_mkdEnd != '/'))
1948  m_mkdEnd++;
1949  while (*m_mkdEnd == '/')
1950  *m_mkdEnd++ = 0;
1951  m_cwdContext = CWD_MKDIR;
1952  ftp->ChangeWorkingDirectory (m_mkdPtr);
1953  }
1954  break;
1955  case CWD_MKDIR:
1956  case CWD_ROOT:
1957  m_mkdPtr = m_mkdEnd;
1958  if (*m_mkdEnd == 0)
1959  {
1960  const char* const msgs [] =
1961  { "mkdir finished", 0 };
1962 
1963  Release (0, msgs, 0, 0);
1964  return;
1965  }
1966  while ((*m_mkdEnd != 0) && (*m_mkdEnd != '/'))
1967  m_mkdEnd++;
1968  while (*m_mkdEnd == '/')
1969  *m_mkdEnd++ = 0;
1970  m_cwdContext = CWD_MKDIR;
1971  ftp->ChangeWorkingDirectory (m_mkdPtr);
1972  break;
1973  default:
1974  {
1975  const char* const msgs [] =
1976  { "mkdir failed, illegal context", 0 };
1977 
1978  Release (FtpIllegalCwdContext, msgs, 0, 0);
1979  return; // don't delete this statement
1980  }
1981  break;
1982  }
1983 }

2103 /****************************************************************/
2104 /* Many functions (FTP callbacks and helpers invoked by them) in*/
2105 /* this file use common collection of input parameters. Their */
2106 /* meaning is explained in this comment block. Throughout of */
2107 /* this file they will be referred as 'common FTP parameters'. */
2108 /* These parameters are: */
2109 /* - ftp: object which executes FTP request. It is used to */
2110 /* access its public properties (to get or set FTP transfer */
2111 /* parameters) and methods (to invoke FTP protocol commands) */
2112 /* - context: there is a small set of different situations in */
2113 /* which FTP callbacks are invoked, for example: when a FTP */
2114 /* control message is sent or received, when a piece of data */
2115 /* is being sent or received, etc. This situation is */
2116 /* considered a context in which an FTP event is handeled and */
2117 /* its callback function is called accordingly. Information */
2118 /* about this context is very helpful in all situations where */
2119 /* some event should appear in different situations */
2120 /* - status: indicates outcome of FTP action handeled by given */
2121 /* callback method. It should be success, failure or error */
2122 /* - state: every possible FTP event is associated with its own */
2123 /* state. In fact they are synonyms although they have */
2124 /* different names, for example: StorFinished is state name, */
2125 /* StoreFinishedEvent is event name. There are many different */
2126 /* states although they are almost not used, especially by */
2127 /* FTP object itself. But nevertheless they are helpful in */
2128 /* some conflicting situations, for example in resolving some */
2129 /* errors which should not be considered true errors, like */
2130 /* listing non existing files, etc. */
2131 /* - args: collection of arguments. This collection is prepared */
2132 /* by 'FTP runtime' and is strongly dependent of FTP event */
2133 /* which triggered callback execution. Every FTP event has its*/
2134 /* own collection of arguments: sizes of collections are */
2135 /* different, types of members in different collections are */
2136 /* different although they are typed as void* and must be cast*/
2137 /* approprietly before use */
2138 /****************************************************************/
2139 
2140 /****************************************************************/
2141 /* Function: FtpClientWorker::Store_PwdFinishedEventHandler()*/
2142 /* In: common FTP parameters */
2143 /* Out: / */
2144 /* In/Out: / */
2145 /* Return: / */
2146 /* Description: PWD handler in 'store file' operation. This */
2147 /* handler is called once the connection has been */
2148 /* established and it is not invoked again for */
2149 /* example for another FTP request if it shares */
2150 /* alive FTP object with previous request. It */
2151 /* remembers FTP home directory and tries to change*/
2152 /* working directory to remote directory contained */
2153 /* in 'store file' request */
2154 /****************************************************************/

2703 void FtpClientWorker::StoreAll_StoreNextFile (FtpClient *ftp, FtpContext context, FtpStatus status, FtpState state,
2704  void* args [])
2705 {
2706  ExceptionFileList* exceptions = m_storeAllFiles->exceptions;
2707 
2708  while (true)
2709  {
2710  if (readdir_r (m_localDir, &m_localDirEntry, &m_localDirEntryPtr) != 0)
2711  {
2712  const char* const args [] =
2713  { "storeall: readdir (", m_storeAllFiles->localDirName, ") failed", 0 };
2714  Release (FtpStoreAllLocDirRead, args, "readdir_r", errno);
2715  return;
2716  }
2717  if (m_localDirEntryPtr == NULL)
2718  {
2719  const char* const msgs [] =
2720  { "storeall finished", 0 };
2721 
2722  Release (0, msgs, 0, 0);
2723  return;
2724  }
2725 
2726  ExceptionFileList* exPtr;
2727  bool exception;
2728  for (exception = false, exPtr = exceptions; exPtr != 0; exPtr = exPtr->next)
2729  {
2730  regex_t reg;
2731  if (regcomp (&reg, exPtr->fileNameTemplate, REG_EXTENDED) == 0)
2732  {
2733  regmatch_t match;
2734  memset (&match, 0, sizeof(regmatch_t));
2735  if (regexec (&reg, m_localDirEntry.d_name, 1, &match, 0) == 0)
2736  if (exPtr->action == ExceptionDeny)
2737  exception = true;
2738  regfree (&reg);
2739  }
2740  }
2741 
2742  if (exception)
2743  continue;
2744 
2745  string localPathName = m_storeAllFiles->localDirName;
2746  localPathName += '/';
2747  localPathName += m_localDirEntry.d_name;
2748 
2749  struct stat sbuff;
2750  if (stat (localPathName.c_str (), &sbuff) != 0)
2751  {
2752  const char* const args [] =
2753  { "storeall: stat (", (char*) localPathName.c_str (), ") failed", 0 };
2754  Release (FtpStoreAllStat, args, "stat", errno);
2755  return;
2756  }
2757  if (sbuff.st_mode & __S_IFREG)
2758  break;
2759  }
2760  if (m_ftpRequest->flags & FTP_PROTECT_EXISTING_FILE)
2761  {
2762  m_listReply = "";
2763  ftp->NameList (m_localDirEntry.d_name);
2764  }
2765  else
2766  ftp->Delete (m_localDirEntry.d_name);
2767 }

3824 void FtpClientWorker::CleanDir_DeleteNextComponent (FtpClient *ftp, FtpContext context, FtpStatus status,
3825  FtpState state, void* args [])
3826 {
3827  while (m_listRead < m_listPtr)
3828  {
3829  char* line = m_listRead;
3830  char* ptr = strstr (m_listRead, "\r\n");
3831  if (ptr != NULL)
3832  {
3833  *ptr = 0;
3834  m_listRead = ptr + 2;
3835  }
3836  else
3837  m_listRead = m_listPtr;
3838 
3839  DirEntryInfo ent;
3840 
3841  if (!ReadListLine (line, ent))
3842  continue;
3843 
3844  if (ent.type == DT_DIR)
3845  {
3846  if (!(m_ftpRequest->flags & FTP_RECURSIVE_OPERATION))
3847  continue;
3848  CleanDir_IncStack ();
3849  ftp->ChangeWorkingDirectory (ent.name);
3850  }
3851  else if (ent.type == DT_REG)
3852  ftp->Delete (ent.name);
3853  else
3854  continue;
3855 
3856  return;
3857  }
3858  if (m_listRead >= m_listPtr)
3859  {
3860  if (m_stackDepth < 0)
3861  {
3862  const char* const msgs [] =
3863  { "clean directory finished finished", 0 };
3864 
3865  Release (0, msgs, 0, 0);
3866  }
3867  else
3868  {
3869  CleanDir_DecStack ();
3870  ftp->ChangeToParentDirectory ();
3871  }
3872  }
3873 }

3875 void FtpClientWorker::CleanDir_IncStack ()
3876 {
3877  if (m_stackDepth + 1 >= m_stackSize)
3878  {
3879  int stackSize = m_stackSize;
3880  stackSize >>= 4;
3881  stackSize++;
3882  stackSize <<= 4;
3883  int* stack = (int*) malloc (2 * stackSize * sizeof(int));
3884  if (stack == 0)
3885  {
3886  const char* const msgs [] =
3887  { "malloc failed", 0 };
3888 
3889  Release (FtpCleanDirMallocFailed, msgs, 0, 0);
3890  return;
3891  }
3892  if (m_stack != 0)
3893  {
3894  memcpy (stack, m_stack, 3 * (m_stackDepth + 1) * sizeof(int));
3895  free (m_stack);
3896  }
3897  m_stack = stack;
3898  m_stackSize = stackSize;
3899  }
3900  m_stackDepth++;
3901  m_stack [3 * m_stackDepth] = m_listStart - m_listBuffer;
3902  m_stack [3 * m_stackDepth + 1] = m_listRead - m_listBuffer;
3903  m_stack [3 * m_stackDepth + 2] = m_listName - m_listBuffer;
3904 }
3905 
3906 void FtpClientWorker::CleanDir_DecStack ()
3907 {
3908  if (m_stackDepth < 0)
3909  return;
3910  m_listPtr = m_listStart;
3911  m_listStart = m_listBuffer + m_stack [3 * m_stackDepth];
3912  m_listRead = m_listBuffer + m_stack [3 * m_stackDepth + 1];
3913  m_listName = m_listBuffer + m_stack [3 * m_stackDepth + 2];
3914  m_stackDepth--;
3915 }

3940 bool FtpClientWorker::ReadListLine (char* line, DirEntryInfo &ent)
3941 {
3942  char* parts [16];
3943  int count;
3944 
3945  bool param;
3946  for (param = false, count = 0; (count < 16) && (*line != 0); ++line)
3947  {
3948  if ((*line == ' ') || (*line == '\t') || (*line == '\r') || (*line == '\n'))
3949  {
3950  param = false;
3951  *line = 0;
3952  continue;
3953  }
3954  if (param)
3955  continue;
3956  parts [count++] = line;
3957  param = true;
3958  }
3959 
3960  memset (&ent, 0, sizeof(DirEntryInfo));
3961  switch (m_sysType)
3962  {
3963  case UnixSystem:
3964  return ReadUnixListLine (parts, count, ent);
3965  break;
3966  case LinuxSystem:
3967  return ReadLinuxListLine (parts, count, ent);
3968  break;
3969  case WindowsSystem:
3970  return ReadWindowsListLine (parts, count, ent);
3971  break;
3972  default:
3973  return false;
3974  break;
3975  }
3976  return false;
3977 }
